724455f-a.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 81st Street (West)
724455f-a.text:
West End Avenue, at, adjoining and south of the S. W. corner of West 81st Strwet (right), showing four of the five frame shacks at this location. These bore No's 339 to 331 inclusive. To the right is the brick wall of No. 306 West 81st Street, a structure erected su'se. uent to 1891 and replacing a frame builiing. Bromleys Atlas of that year shows the last of the West End shacks; their edition, 1897, disclosing the Avenue
frontage cleared.
Various authorities have located this view as being
the N. E. corner of Fifth Avenue and 81st Street. The New York Post of October 1e32 published same in their ;ravure section. The Collection of J. Clarence D vies at the Museum of the City of New York has a copy. The Fifth Avenue Bank during its Centenial week exhibited a copy from the Robert Friedenberg Collection.
Brown Brothers, photographers, whose imprint appears
on the back of this, gave the location as Amsterdam Avenue and
81st Street.
